These words describe how outgoing or sociable a Protagonist is judged to be by a (usually implicit) Judge, often in a particular context, either with certain people (the Company), or about a particular situation, topic or event (the Content). As opposed to the Social_interaction_evaluation frame, this frame talks about how much someone interacts, not how well.

companionable.a, extrovert.n, friendly.a, gregarious.a, introverted.a, loner.n, outgoing.a, recluse.n, shy.a, sociable.a, timid.a
